The paper proposes a novel method for patient subgroup detection using convex optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The approach is also tailored towards precision medicine, which involves developing personalized treatment schemes for different patient subgroups (cs.AI). The paper applies the method to prioritize risk factors for hypertension in a vulnerable demographic subgroup, which involves analyzing medical data (cs.CE). The method involves clustering and prioritizing input variables, which are common techniques in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of identifying and prioritizing risk factors, which is a common theme in health informatics and medical data analysis (cs.SI).
